<title>Condition to Char Tag</title>
<shortdesc>Assigns character tags to content based on conditional
tagging.</shortdesc>
<prolog><author>Scott Prentice</author>
<author>scottp</author>
<critdates><created date = "2013-01-19"/>
<revised modified = "2016-03-05"/></critdates></prolog>
<body><p status = "changed"><indexterm>conditions<indexterm>to character
tags</indexterm></indexterm>This command requires setup to the CondToCharTag
section of the <filepath>fm2dita.ini</filepath> file. Once this
INI section is updated with condname/chartag pairs, run it on a
file or book to replace conditional ranges with the specified character
tags in all files.</p>
<p status = "changed">The <cmdname conref = "_shared.xml#id131KC0I0VHS/cmd_ren-conds"></cmdname> command
could be used to clean up condition naming before using the this
command. It is always best to use the <cmdname conref = "_shared.xml#id131KC0I0VHS/cmd_show-conds"></cmdname> command before
using this command.</p></body></topic>
